Your orchestrator is cec50b17:0. Work inside `.synapse/worktrees/developer-25-manual-proposal-trigger`. Commit your changes. Do not push.

Three changes:

---

## Change 1 — Remove auto-spawn from --task-id eval path (src/index.ts)

In the `synapse eval --task-id` action handler, find the loop after `writeEvalResults(taskId, evalRows)`:

```typescript
for (const r of evalRows) {
  if (!r.passed) {
    const triggered = checkAndResetMetricThreshold(r.metric);
    if (triggered) {
      await spawnProposalSession(taskId, r.metric);
      process.stdout.write(`  → threshold reached for ${r.metric}, spawned proposal session\n`);
    }
  }
}
```

Remove the `spawnProposalSession` call and everything that imports it. Keep `checkAndResetMetricThreshold` — but now instead of auto-spawning, just print which metric hit the threshold so the operator knows to click "Generate proposal" in the UI:

```typescript
for (const r of evalRows) {
  if (!r.passed) {
    const triggered = checkAndResetMetricThreshold(r.metric);
    if (triggered) {
      process.stdout.write(`  ⚠ threshold reached for metric: ${r.metric} — click "Generate proposal" in S-Deck Eval tab\n`);
    }
  }
}
```

Remove the `spawnProposalSession` import from this path. Keep `checkAndResetMetricThreshold`.

---

## Change 2 — New dashboard endpoint: POST /api/proposals/generate (src/dashboard.ts)

Add a new endpoint that manually triggers proposal generation for a specific metric:

```typescript
app.post('/api/proposals/generate', async (req: Request, res: Response) => {
  const { metric } = req.body as { metric: string };
  if (!metric) { res.status(400).json({ error: 'metric required' }); return; }

  // Dynamically import spawnProposalSession
  const { spawnProposalSession } = await import('./eval/propose.js');
  const { getFailedTasksForMetric } = await import('./db.js');

  // Get most recent failed task for this metric to pass as triggerTaskId
  const failedIds = getFailedTasksForMetric(metric, 1);
  const triggerTaskId = failedIds[0] ?? 0;

  // Spawn the proposal session (fire-and-forget)
  spawnProposalSession(triggerTaskId, metric);

  res.json({ ok: true, message: `Spawning proposal session for metric: ${metric}` });
});
```

---

## Change 3 — Frontend: "Generate proposal" button per metric (public/app.js)

In `renderEval()`, update the metric counters bar. Currently it looks like:

```javascript
const counterHtml = `<div class="eval-counters">
  ${METRICS.map(m => {
    const count = counts[m] ?? 0;
    const color = count >= THRESHOLD ? 'var(--p0)' : count >= 2 ? 'var(--warn)' : 'var(--muted)';
    return `<div class="eval-counter">
      <span style="color:${color}">${m}: ${count}/${THRESHOLD}</span>
    </div>`;
  }).join('')}
</div>`;
```

Change it to show a "Generate proposal" button when count >= THRESHOLD:

```javascript
const counterHtml = `<div class="eval-counters">
  ${METRICS.map(m => {
    const count = counts[m] ?? 0;
    const color = count >= THRESHOLD ? 'var(--p0)' : count >= 2 ? 'var(--warn)' : 'var(--muted)';
    const btn = count >= THRESHOLD
      ? `<button class="btn-gen-proposal" data-metric="${esc(m)}" style="margin-left:6px;font-size:9px;padding:1px 6px">Generate proposal</button>`
      : '';
    return `<div class="eval-counter" style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:4px">
      <span style="color:${color}">${m}: ${count}/${THRESHOLD}</span>
      ${btn}
    </div>`;
  }).join('')}
</div>`;
```

Wire up the button via event delegation on `#eval-content` (or directly after setting innerHTML):

```javascript
// After setting el.innerHTML, wire the generate buttons
el.querySelectorAll('.btn-gen-proposal').forEach(btn => {
  btn.addEventListener('click', async () => {
    const metric = btn.dataset.metric;
    btn.disabled = true;
    btn.textContent = 'Spawning…';
    try {
      await fetch('/api/proposals/generate', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ metric }),
      });
      btn.textContent = 'Spawned ✓';
    } catch {
      btn.textContent = 'Error';
    }
  });
});
```

---

## Change 4 — Pass metric context into the proposal prompt (src/eval/propose.ts)

In `spawnProposalSession`, the handover doc already mentions the trigger metric. Find the section with "## Trigger metric:" and ensure it also includes a human-readable description of the threshold that was violated. Update the handover doc to be more explicit about what failed and why the proposal is being generated:

Find the existing handover doc content in `spawnProposalSession` and add a "## Why this proposal was triggered" section near the top:

```
## Why this proposal was triggered
The metric **${triggerMetric}** has accumulated ${limit} consecutive failures since the last protocol update. 
This proposal should focus specifically on fixing this metric. Do not address other metrics.
```

Replace the existing trigger description lines with this more explicit version.

---

Build `npm run build` and verify clean.

